From: jem@snakemail.hut.fi (Johan Myreen)
Subject: WARNING! (Was: OS-BS v2.0 Beta8 released (Yet another boot loader))
Date: 22 Oct 93 14:45:13 GMT

In article <2a7iit$94c@samba.oit.unc.edu> thomas@aeon.in-berlin.de (Thomas Wolfram) writes:

>Hi,

>   OS Boot Select is a replacement of the ordinary master boot
>   program. It provides a customizable boot menu with a timeout

...

>In the moment os-bs needs except the Master Boot Record the space of four
>(will probably grow) additional sectors. For this it uses the almost always
                                          ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
>unused sectors 2, 3, 4, 5 on cylinder 0, head 0, disk 0 for which it computes
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
>a simple 'xor' checksum. But this place will be selectable in the future.

Warning! This area is a "No Man's Land" that might be in use. "Almost
always unused" is not good enough. CHECK if this is the case on you
machine before installing the above mentioned boot loader.

For example, my machine uses this area of the disk to store the disk
geometry; the BIOS reads it at boot time. If this info overwritten the
machine will most probably not boot at all.

-- 
Johan Myreen
jem@cs.hut.fi
60 11'55" N, 24 53'30" E

