From: Harald.T.Alvestrand@uninett.no
Subject: 3331 Linux users counted
Date: 22 Oct 1993 15:11:21 GMT

Hello, all!
No even thousand mark passed this time.
But I'll be away, or too busy to work on this, for about 2 weeks
now, so I thought I'd just post this.
Registration seems to be levelling out at about 35 E-mails per day,
at this speed it will take us 7.5 years to register 100.000 users.

I intend to post this on the 1st of every month in c.o.l.misc, but
haven't yet found a piece of software to do posting from a script.
(Hint, hint....)

Registering other people, to allow registration of non-Email users,
is awaiting 2 things:

- Time to implement something
- A deep thought about the privacy issues involved.
  Discussion on c.o.l.misc of this is encouraged!
  
(In particular: If I publish, is privacy respected? If I don't publish,
how can people tell that others have registered them more than once?)

To join the count, send a message to linux-counter@uninett.no (NOT TO ME!!!)
with the subject lines

   I use Linux at home
   I use Linux at work
   I use Linux at home and at work
   I don't use Linux

(the last one is for the one who just wiped Linux off his harddisk and
went back to MS-DOS :-)

In all cases, you will get an E-mail with the current count back.
Mail from the same address will only be counted once, so if you want to
change your vote, just send another mail.

Happy Linuxing!

                   Harald Tveit Alvestrand

